│ the Issue:\nThe IPSCCP pass replaced an fcmp une with a constant splat true   │
│ inside a function with attribute \"denormal-fp-math\"=\"ieee,dynamic\". This  │
│ is incorrect because under dynamic denormal handling, denormal inputs are     │
│ treated as unknown at compile time; they may be flushed to zero or kept as    │
│ IEEE denormals at runtime. Specifically, comparing a denormal value against   │
│ zero using UNE can be true (IEEE) or false (flush-to-zero), so folding to     │
│ true is unsound.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe SCCP debug output shows it   │
│ merged a constant <2 x i1> splat(true) into the fcmp. Alive2 demonstrates a   │
│ counterexample with lane 0 false and lane 1 true, which is legal under        │
│ dynamic denormal handling, hence the transformation is incorrect.\n\n3. Root  │
│ Cause Analysis:\nThe first transformation is triggered by                     │
│ SCCPSolver::tryToReplaceWithConstant, which uses                              │
│ SCCPInstVisitor::getConstantOrNull. The constant came from                    │
│ SCCPInstVisitor::visitCmpInst, which calls                                    │
│ ValueLatticeElement::getCompare(..., DL) to fold                              │
│ comparisons.\n\nValueLatticeElement::getCompare uses                          │
│ ConstantFoldCompareInstOperands(Pred, C0, C1, DL) without providing the       │
│ instruction context. In ConstantFolding.cpp, denormal-aware folding relies on │
│ FlushFPConstant(Operand, I, ...) which needs the Instruction* to query the    │
│ function's denormal-fp-math mode. If I is null, FlushFPConstant becomes a     │
│ no-op. Consequently, folding proceeds as if denormals are IEEE, incorrectly   │
│ producing true for (denorm != 0.0).\n\nThus, SCCP/ValueLattice missed passing │
│ the Instruction* to constant folding, so denormal dynamic modes were          │
│ ignored.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\n- Edit Point 1:                       │
│ llvm/include/llvm/Analysis/ValueLattice.h (around declaration of              │
│ getCompare)\n  Change the declaration of ValueLatticeElement::getCompare to   │
│ accept an optional const Instruction* parameter with a default of nullptr.    │
│ Also ensure Instruction is forward-declared in this header, since it only     │
│ includes Constants.h/ConstantRange today.\n  Rationale: This allows callers   │
│ that have instruction context (like SCCP) to provide it so ConstantFolding    │
│ can respect denormal modes.\n\n- Edit Point 2:                                │
│ llvm/lib/Analysis/ValueLattice.cpp (file header untouched; ensure includes    │
│ are sufficient)\n  Adjust the definition signature of                         │
│ ValueLatticeElement::getCompare to take the new const Instruction *I          │
│ parameter. Update the internal call to ConstantFoldCompareInstOperands to     │
│ pass I through: ConstantFoldCompareInstOperands(Pred, getConstant(),          │
│ Other.getConstant(), DL, /*TLI=*/nullptr, I). No other behavioral change.\n   │
│ Rationale: Propagates instruction context to denormal-aware constant          │
│ folding.\n\n- Edit Point 3: llvm/lib/Analysis/ValueLattice.cpp (actual        │
│ function body lines 14-30 as shown) \n  Replace the existing getCompare       │
│ definition with the new one including the Instruction* parameter and          │
│ forwarding it. The rest of the function logic remains the same so integer     │
│ range comparisons and equality-not-constant cases continue to work.\n\n- Edit │
│ Point 4: llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SCCPSolver.cpp (visitCmpInst at ~1607)\n   │
│ Update the call to getCompare to pass &I (the CmpInst) as the instruction     │
│ context:\n    Constant *C = V1State.getCompare(I.getPredicate(), I.getType(), │
│ V2State, DL, &I);\n  Rationale: Ensures SCCP's folding of compares is         │
│ denormal-mode aware. With \"ieee,dynamic\" and a denormal constant,           │
│ ConstantFoldCompareInstOperands will return nullptr (FlushFPConstant returns  │
│ nullptr for dynamic denormal mode), preventing SCCP from incorrectly marking  │
│ the compare as a constant.\n\nNotes:\n- Other call sites (LazyValueInfo,      │
│ FunctionSpecialization) can continue to call the method without the new       │
│ parameter; the default nullptr preserves current behavior. If desired, they   │
│ can be incrementally updated later wherever an instruction is available.\n-   │
│ We add a forward declaration of class Instruction in ValueLattice.h to avoid  │
│ pulling in heavy headers.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nBy threading the instruction     │
│ context through ValueLatticeElement::getCompare and using it in SCCP's        │
│ visitCmpInst, constant folding of floating-point comparisons will honor       │
│ denormal-fp-math modes. Under ieee,dynamic, folding of comparisons with       │
│ denormal constants now returns nullptr (unknown), preventing ipsccp from      │
│ replacing the compare with a constant. This fixes the incorrect               │
│ transformation observed in the reproducer."})                                 │
