│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The IPSCCP pass replaced an fcmp une with a constant splat true inside a      │
│ function with attribute "denormal-fp-math"="ieee,dynamic". This is incorrect  │
│ because under dynamic denormal handling, denormal inputs are treated as       │
│ unknown at compile time; they may be flushed to zero or kept as IEEE          │
│ denormals at runtime. Specifically, comparing a denormal value against zero   │
│ using UNE can be true (IEEE) or false (flush-to-zero), so folding to true is  │
│ unsound.                                                                      │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ The SCCP debug output shows it merged a constant <2 x i1> splat(true) into    │
│ the fcmp. Alive2 demonstrates a counterexample with lane 0 false and lane 1   │
│ true, which is legal under dynamic denormal handling, hence the               │
│ transformation is incorrect.                                                  │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ The first transformation is triggered by                                      │
│ SCCPSolver::tryToReplaceWithConstant, which uses                              │
│ SCCPInstVisitor::getConstantOrNull. The constant came from                    │
│ SCCPInstVisitor::visitCmpInst, which calls                                    │
│ ValueLatticeElement::getCompare(..., DL) to fold comparisons.                 │
│                                                                               │
│ ValueLatticeElement::getCompare uses ConstantFoldCompareInstOperands(Pred,    │
│ C0, C1, DL) without providing the instruction context. In                     │
│ ConstantFolding.cpp, denormal-aware folding relies on                         │
│ FlushFPConstant(Operand, I, ...) which needs the Instruction* to query the    │
│ function's denormal-fp-math mode. If I is null, FlushFPConstant becomes a     │
│ no-op. Consequently, folding proceeds as if denormals are IEEE, incorrectly   │
│ producing true for (denorm != 0.0).                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Thus, SCCP/ValueLattice missed passing the Instruction* to constant folding,  │
│ so denormal dynamic modes were ignored.                                       │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ - Edit Point 1: llvm/include/llvm/Analysis/ValueLattice.h (around declaration │
│ of getCompare)                                                                │
│   Change the declaration of ValueLatticeElement::getCompare to accept an      │
│ optional const Instruction* parameter with a default of nullptr. Also ensure  │
│ Instruction is forward-declared in this header, since it only includes        │
│ Constants.h/ConstantRange today.                                              │
│   Rationale: This allows callers that have instruction context (like SCCP) to │
│ provide it so ConstantFolding can respect denormal modes.                     │
│                                                                               │
│ - Edit Point 2: llvm/lib/Analysis/ValueLattice.cpp (file header untouched;    │
│ ensure includes are sufficient)                                               │
│   Adjust the definition signature of ValueLatticeElement::getCompare to take  │
│ the new const Instruction *I parameter. Update the internal call to           │
│ ConstantFoldCompareInstOperands to pass I through:                            │
│ ConstantFoldCompareInstOperands(Pred, getConstant(), Other.getConstant(), DL, │
│ /*TLI=*/nullptr, I). No other behavioral change.                              │
│   Rationale: Propagates instruction context to denormal-aware constant        │
│ folding.                                                                      │
│                                                                               │
│ - Edit Point 3: llvm/lib/Analysis/ValueLattice.cpp (actual function body      │
│ lines 14-30 as shown)                                                         │
│   Replace the existing getCompare definition with the new one including the   │
│ Instruction* parameter and forwarding it. The rest of the function logic      │
│ remains the same so integer range comparisons and equality-not-constant cases │
│ continue to work.                                                             │
│                                                                               │
│ - Edit Point 4: llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SCCPSolver.cpp (visitCmpInst at     │
│ ~1607)                                                                        │
│   Update the call to getCompare to pass &I (the CmpInst) as the instruction   │
│ context:                                                                      │
│     Constant *C = V1State.getCompare(I.getPredicate(), I.getType(), V2State,  │
│ DL, &I);                                                                      │
│   Rationale: Ensures SCCP's folding of compares is denormal-mode aware. With  │
│ "ieee,dynamic" and a denormal constant, ConstantFoldCompareInstOperands will  │
│ return nullptr (FlushFPConstant returns nullptr for dynamic denormal mode),   │
│ preventing SCCP from incorrectly marking the compare as a constant.           │
│                                                                               │
│ Notes:                                                                        │
│ - Other call sites (LazyValueInfo, FunctionSpecialization) can continue to    │
│ call the method without the new parameter; the default nullptr preserves      │
│ current behavior. If desired, they can be incrementally updated later         │
│ wherever an instruction is available.                                         │
│ - We add a forward declaration of class Instruction in ValueLattice.h to      │
│ avoid pulling in heavy headers.                                               │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ By threading the instruction context through ValueLatticeElement::getCompare  │
│ and using it in SCCP's visitCmpInst, constant folding of floating-point       │
│ comparisons will honor denormal-fp-math modes. Under ieee,dynamic, folding of │
│ comparisons with denormal constants now returns nullptr (unknown), preventing │
│ ipsccp from replacing the compare with a constant. This fixes the incorrect   │
│ transformation observed in the reproducer.                                    │
